snippet: This year may well be remembered as the most numbing ever for mainstream rock.
abstract: Jon Caramanica complains about the current state of rock music, saying musicians and old bands are merely spinning their wheels and going through the motions with tired formulas and little innovation; says 2011 may well be remembered as the most numbing ever for mainstream rock.
lead_paragraph: This year may well be remembered as the most numbing ever for mainstream rock.

headline.seo: Rock in 2011: Hot Chelle Rae, Foster the People, Chevelle
headline.main: The Year When Rock Just Spun Its Wheels
headline.print_headline: The Year When Rock Just Spun Its Wheels
